data.content:
This is a well-known breaking change: **ASP.NET Core 10 upgrades from Microsoft.OpenApi v1 → v2**, which redesigns the object model for OpenAPI 3.1 / JSON Schema alignment. Here are the three breaking areas in your code and the fixes:

---

### 1. `OpenApiString` removed — use `JsonNode`

The entire `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace (`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc.) is gone. `Schema.Example` is now a `JsonNode`.

```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

---

### 2. `OpenApiSecurityScheme` + `OpenApiReference` pattern replaced

v2 introduces dedicated reference types. Instead of creating a scheme and setting a `Reference` property, use `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` directly:

```csharp
// Before
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// After
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};
```

---

### 3. `Nullable` property removed — use `JsonSchemaType` flags

OpenAPI 3.1 aligns with JSON Schema, which represents nullability via `type: ["string", "null"]` instead of a separate `nullable` keyword. The `Type` property is now a `[Flags]` enum:

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

You may need `using Microsoft.OpenApi;` for the `JsonSchemaType` enum.

---

### Final corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**TL;DR**: `OpenApiAny` types → `JsonNode`, reference wrappers → dedicated `*Reference` types, `Nullable` → `JsonSchemaType.Null` flag.
